Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

In a #medium pot{}, combine @farro{1/2%cup}, @water{3%cups}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. (Be sure to measure the farro; we sent more.)

Bring to a boil and cook until farro is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> If you end up with any excess stock, simply pour it out. Alternatively, if stock evaporates before farro is done, add a splash of water.

While farro cooks, cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered) (for 4 servings, zest 1 lemon and quarter both). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced).

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tablespoon}, salt, and @pepper{}. Add half the lemon wedges, peel sides up.

Roast until broccoli is browned and tender and lemon is lightly browned, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @pork chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with remaining @Italian seasoning{1/2%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> If pork begins to brown too quickly, lower heat.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

To same pan over medium-high heat, add garlic, remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat; stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Add a squeeze of fresh lemon juice.

Stir roasted broccoli, @butter{1%tablespoon}, a squeeze of fresh lemon juice, and lemon zest to taste into pot with farro. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide farro between plates; top with pork. Drizzle pan sauce over pork. Serve with roasted lemon wedges on the side.